Gedit Find Open Plugin
Copyright (C) 2010 Mario Zaizar <mariozaizar@gmail.com>

INSTALLATION

1) Go to http://github.com/mariozaizar/gedit-findopen-plugin, then select the Download section.
2) Download the file, and then extract the contents in your computer.
3) Copy all files to ~/.gnome2/gedit/plugins path (for personal use only). 
   If you have installed gmate, you can copy to /usr/lib/gedit-2/plugins/ (to wide system use). 
   Note: You will need root permission.
4) Fire up gedit, go to Edit > Preferences, select the plugins tab, and make sure "Find Open" is checked.
